dct_description_sm: Printed with vegetation. Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (AM), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , original map compiled by USGS , area along Wabash River in part by Corps of Engineers, U. S. Army. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Lafayette, Indiana : Tippecanoe County. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3664 IV NW. AMS 1. "A.M.S. Series V851" "Transverse Mercator projection." Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, schools, churches, cemeteries, mines, and natural features. "Contour interval 10 feet." Marginal maps: Index to boundaries.--Index to adjoining sheets. "Scale changed, marginal data revised and Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, 1948. Copied in 1948 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Lafayette, 1942. Original map compiled by USGS, area along Wabash River in part by Corps of Engineers, U. S. Army, 1929. Surveyed in 1940." "N4022.5-W8652.5/7.5." "AMS 1, 1949." "3-49."
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army, 1948.
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:25,000
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army Map Service; Geological Survey (U.S.)
